node.text:
As some of you may know, someone has been aggressively stalking, harassing and impersonating me for the past year. This person has threatened me, slashed my tires, and done a bunch of other gruesome things that I don’t want to even talk about because I think that will give them satisfaction. This person has tried everything under the sun to try and ruin my reputation, humiliate me and break me down. They have involved my family members, my work and are continuing to impersonate me right now. I have a hard time feeling safe but like many of
you have found that training has been the only way I have been able to get through this. I posted a photo a few days ago with a gun. I wanted to clarify something, I am not a gun nut, but making multiple police reports and fbi reports and having them tell me there is nothing they can do until I am harmed I felt I needed a way to protect myself. So this is a video made by @fitdocproductions briefly going over a trip I made to Texas to tell them a little bit about my story and how to learn how to protect myself. Please have an open mind and understand where I am coming from. Also, PLEASE DO NOT SEND ANYONE PRETENDING TO BE ME MONEY! I would never ask you to do that! Thank you guys!

node.text: I rarely share my personal life on instagram. However this last weekend something happened that I wanted to share! Before you unfollow me thinking I am changing my content to fluffy romantic stuff, I’m not I just think it’s important to give you more of an understanding of who I am. My husband and I have been together since 2013 and we met in medical school. I wouldn’t even be on instagram writing this or have been a fitness model if it wasn’t for him. He’s been there supporting me and loving me for who I am every step of the way. Video done by the incredible @gilcoproductions!!!

node.text: After being stuck in bed for two weeks with COVID I tried to make up for it this week by training twice a day. I’m definitely not where I was before I got sick but slowly regaining strength. Overall I lost 6lbs from when I got sick to the day I started training again. That’s a large amount of weight for me considering my stage weight and off season weight are only 10lbs apart. Anyways, doing the best that I can and super grateful I recovered as fast as I did. ❤️💪 @loungeunderwear

node.text: Building muscle density does not happen overnight. This is years of playing soccer, running track and of course lifting weights. My progression has not been linear over all but from year to year I have been consistent and can see that I’m actually making progress and that’s enough to keep me going! Little by little, a little becomes A LOT! @sycompetitionsuits @mrolympiallc @milwaukeepro_titanopen

node.text: Looks fade, character does not. My body is a canvas that allows me to display my discipline and hard work, however who I am as a person is far more important to me. As I’ve talked about before, body building is my escape and it’s just a added bonus it you can see physical progress. However, throughout the day I don’t perseverate about how many inches my waist is or how many lbs I weigh. This detachment from my physical appearance allows me to not have an emotional relationship with my body and instead a practical one. I hear clients tell me that they’re so mad at their body for holding water or angry they can’t grow their calves, however having this type of you vs your body mentality is the road block between you and your progress. Basically when I was concerned with how I looked, I was never as happy. Now that I just stick to lifting and weighing my food and not obsessing over numbers progress comes much easier. @surraca @loungeunderwear

node.text: Body building is deeper than liking how something looks. It’s about knowing why and how something looks the way it does. Appreciating that amount of work that goes into a certain form. I couldn’t lift 30lbs over my head 7 years ago when I started, so although I look different, it’s nothing compared to how different I feel. 💪🏽 photo by @gilcoproductions suit by @suitsusexy SAVE 15% off if you use my code: Sunny15
